item.title: Anyone with a favorite NON-Electronic song?
item.dc:creator: akabillposters
item.description:
NotMiles:

Pretty much anything by Snarky Puppy

Indeed! Yes and yes.
Haven’t seen them live yet, but as modern ensembles go, they’re challenging Jaga Jazzist (who are awesome live) for the top spot on my love list. (I wouldn’t call them strictly ‘non-electronic’ though. Certainly not electronic by genre. They’re fusion enough to have lashing of fonky/jazz AF Moog when it counts c/o that grand chap Cory Henry.)

As for a personal ‘non-electronic’ favourite, it’d probably be something from Stevie Wonder ('70s) or Philip Glass.

(Lots to choose from, as I’m not particularly a fan of ‘EDM’.)
